board*.png

# ---- live working data: REAL creator/scraped content (NEVER commit) ----
# These are the operator's live working directories. Every pattern below is
# ANCHORED (it contains a slash, so git resolves it from the repo root) — that
# is deliberate: the curated fixtures under demo/ mirror this same layout and
# must stay committable. Do not rewrite these as bare names like `studio/`.

# Hand-curated real creator targeting lists.
/links.txt
ReelScraper/platforms/*/pages.txt
ReelScraper/platforms/*/creators.txt
ReelScraper/platforms/*/seeds.txt
ReelScraper/platforms/*/keywords.txt
ReelScraper/platforms/*/discovered_pages.txt

# The scored corpus and every run export. `core/runner.py` writes content.json and
# virality_reels.csv straight into platforms/<platform>/ — a directory where, before this
# block, only pages.txt was ignored. `./demo` copies the private demodataset.zip over the
# working tree into exactly these paths, so without them a `git add -A` after one ./demo
# would publish the real dataset. `niche_config.json` is CONFIG and stays tracked.
ReelScraper/platforms/*/content.json
ReelScraper/platforms/*/virality_reels.csv
ReelScraper/platforms/*/*.csv
ReelScraper/platforms/*/*.xlsx
ReelScraper/platforms/*/*_raw.json
ReelScraper/platforms/*/profiles_meta.json
ReelScraper/platforms/*/meta.json

# Cross-agent learnings distilled from real analyzed content (core/memory.py).
ReelScraper/memory/shared/insights.jsonl
ReelScraper/memory/shared/INSIGHTS.md

# Generated reels + the poster/record/index sidecars that carry the source content_id.
# `*.mp4` above covers the video itself; these are everything beside it. Anchored per-entry
# rather than as a bare `renders/`, so a tracked renders/README.md stays possible.
ReelScraper/renders/*/
ReelScraper/renders/index.json
ReelScraper/renders/renders.jsonl

# Producer output + human-gate decision log (derived from real scraped reels).
# Per-platform subdirs only, so the tracked studio/README.md stays tracked.
ReelScraper/studio/*/

# Self-eval / judge results, keyed by real content_ids.
# `evals/*/` covers the per-agent subdirectories (evals/analysis-engine/…) and the two
# glob lines below cover loose result files written directly at evals/ root — without
# them a judge run that emits `evals/<id>.json` instead of `evals/<agent>/<id>.json`
# would be left un-ignored and stageable. A tracked evals/README.md stays possible.
ReelScraper/evals/*/
ReelScraper/evals/evals.jsonl
ReelScraper/evals/*.json
ReelScraper/evals/*.jsonl

# Per-agent runtime config, written by the hub and edited from the Dashboard.
ReelScraper/config/agents/

# ---- the demo dataset ships SEPARATELY, never in the repo ----
# demo-data/data/ holds REAL scraped Instagram data (handles, captions, metrics, derived
# reels). It is NOT tracked: the dataset travels privately as demodataset.zip and ./demo
# unpacks it into demo-data/data/ at runtime. Only the folder README and an empty-dir
# marker are kept, so a fresh clone has the directory but none of the data. Publishing the
# real dataset would expose third-party content without consent — see demo-data/README.md.
#
# Ignore ALL of demo-data/ and re-admit only the two tracked files. The earlier form
# (`/demo-data/data/*`) covered the payload but not `demo-data/manifest.json`, which the zip
# unpacks alongside `data/` — so after a real `./demo` that one file was still stageable.
# Denying the directory and negating the exceptions cannot miss a new sibling the capture
# script starts emitting.
demodataset.zip
/demo-data/*
!/demo-data/README.md
!/demo-data/data/
/demo-data/data/*
!/demo-data/data/.gitkeep
